<!-- ================= STRATEGIES ================= -->
<section id="strategies">
<h2 class="section-title">Investment Strategies</h2>
<p class="section-desc">
Cedar Acquisitions specializes in structured real estate solutions designed to solve complex seller situations.
Each strategy below is deployed selectively based on asset profile, capital structure, and seller objectives.
</p>

<div class="strategy-grid">

<div class="panel">
<h3>Seller Financing</h3>
<h4>Income-Oriented Exit Strategy</h4>
<p>
Seller financing allows property owners to convert equity into a predictable income stream
while maintaining a secured position in the asset. This approach is often used when sellers
prioritize long-term cash flow, tax efficiency, and controlled exit timelines.
</p>
<ul>
<li>Monthly interest-based income</li>
<li>Potential capital gains tax deferral</li>
<li>Flexible amortization and balloon terms</li>
<li>Seller retains senior lien position</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="panel">
<h3>Subject-To Transactions</h3>
<h4>Preserving Existing Financing</h4>
<p>
In a subject-to acquisition, Cedar acquires the property while the existing financing
remains in place. This strategy is often ideal when properties carry below-market interest
rates or when speed of execution is critical.
</p>
<ul>
<li>No refinancing or lender qualification</li>
<li>Preserves favorable interest rates</li>
<li>Accelerated closing timelines</li>
<li>Professional servicing and insurance oversight</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="panel">
<h3>Wrap Mortgages</h3>
<h4>Structured Debt Consolidation</h4>
<p>
Wrap mortgages consolidate underlying debt into a single structured note, providing
clarity, transparency, and simplified cash flow for sellers while maintaining
appropriate legal protections.
</p>
<ul>
<li>Single consolidated payment structure</li>
<li>Clear payoff and exit timelines</li>
<li>Attorney-reviewed documentation</li>
<li>Third-party loan servicing</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="panel">
<h3>Stack Method</h3>
<h4>Hybrid Capital Strategy</h4>
<p>
The Stack Method is Cedar’s proprietary approach combining upfront capital, preferred income,
and refinancing to maximize seller proceeds while minimizing downside exposure.
</p>
<ul>
<li>Immediate liquidity at closing</li>
<li>Ongoing preferred income stream</li>
<li>Enhanced security protections</li>
<li>Designed for complex, high-value assets</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
</section>

